  "prompt": "What is meant by internships?",
  "response": "Internships are structured, short-term work experiences that provide individuals, typically students or recent graduates, with the opportunity to gain practical, hands-on experience in a specific field or industry. Internships can be paid or unpaid and are often used as a stepping stone to full-time employment. They allow individuals to develop professional skills, build a network of contacts, and determine if a particular career path is a good fit for them. Internships can be found in a wide range of industries, from business and technology to healthcare and the arts, and they vary in duration, typically lasting from a few weeks to several months. Employers benefit from internships by cultivating talent, evaluating potential future employees, and completing specific projects or tasks.",
